column5: Myself and a buddy were on the River at 5:30am. I've got access to private property on the Ganny and when we got there we were the only 2 people there. I've been fishing this spot for about 8 years now and it just keeps getting better and better. We fished 14 hours and hooked into 60+ fish between the both of us plus he got 1 navtie brown trout and I got 3. Here are some pic's enjoy!!
Brown wolley bugger was working well in the morning.
good job sounds liek a stellar day
Dude, thats awesome!  sounds like a heeluva good time!
Matt with another steehead and my second native got him with the hares ear!
Matt with another hog and my 3rd native of the day!
It was a great day for fishing!
Looks like a great day for sure. Not one person in your pics on the Ganny, sweet

Its great to have a spot in which is private! hard to come by these days. Even still we get the same guy who comes every year and pretends to know the land owners. When he really doesn't. I've had to kick him off serval times you think he would get the hint.
Oh man awesome stuff, good to know that the fishery is still going strong.
